summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of $6375.42, or so much thereof as may be necessary, from the general fund, to pay the City's portion and the unpaid assessments against private property, for the purpose of paying the judgments obtained in the proceedings for the opening of a public street (Olympia Way) under Ordinance No. 11173 of the City of Seattle, approved the 10th day of August, 1904.
